<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="right-adj">right <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /raɪt/    美 /raɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>对的；正确的；正当的</strong></h4>
<p>反 wrong ： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Rules often tell us what is right or wrong. 
规则往往告诉我们什么是正确的或什么是错误的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is <strong>right to</strong> be kind to other people. 
善待他人是正确的。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>右的；右翼的</strong></h4>
<p>反 left ： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Most people eat, write and work with their right hands. 
多数人用右手吃饭、写字、工作。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>适当的</strong></h4>
<p>反 wrong ： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Learn to say the right thing at the right time. 
学会在适当的时候说适当的话。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>正常的；健全的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you right now? 
你这会儿感觉好吗?</p></div></div>